    "prompt": "<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows two rectangular circuits, labeled Circuit X and Circuit Y. From bottom to top, the left vertical branch of each circuit has a battery with e m f script uppercase E followed by a switch. The right vertical branch of each circuit has a capacitor with capacitance C. The top horizontal branch of each circuit has a resistor with resistance R. In circuit X a resistor with resistance R sub X is on the top horizontal branch, to the right of the other resistor. In circuit Y a resistor with resistance R sub Y is on a middle vertical branch. The middle vertical branch joins the top horizontal branch to the right of the resistor on that branch. A note states that R sub X equals R sub Y, which equals R.\" src=\"/images/154e956de9ae2f58b83d52a5cbbb022d.svg\"></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Two circuits are made using identical batteries, resistors, and capacitors, as shown in the figure. Initially, the switches in both circuits are open and the capacitors are uncharged. The switches are then closed. Which of the following makes a correct claim about the currents in resistors <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"R sub X\"><math alttext=\"R sub X\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>R</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">X</mi></msub></math></span></span> and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"R sub Y\"><math alttext=\"R sub Y\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>R</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Y</mi></msub></math></span></span> immediately after the switches are closed, and provides evidence or reasoning that supports the claim?</p>\n",
    "answer": "i1",
